# Supabase — public client config.
# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill in. NEVER commit real secrets.
#
# Local dev (Supabase CLI/Docker): run `npm run db:status` to print the values
# below. The local anon key + URL are well-known, non-secret CLI defaults and
# are safe to use as-is for local development.
#
# Prod: get these from the hosted Supabase project's API settings (Project URL
# + anon/publishable key). Do NOT put them here — set them in your deploy
# environment (GCP Secret Manager → Cloud Run, per ADR 0003; the CI deploy stub
# binds them by name — see docs/ci.md).

# The Supabase project URL (local default shown).
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321

# The anon (publishable) key. RLS-protected, browser-safe.
# Local CLI default below; replace with the hosted anon key in prod.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZS1kZW1vIiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJleHAiOjE5ODM4MTI5OTZ9.CRXP1A7WOeoJeXxjNni43kdQwgnWNReilDMblYTn_I0

# NOTE (ADR 0003): there is intentionally NO SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY here.
# M0/M1 do all data access as the signed-in user so RLS is always in force.
# The service-role key is reserved for the M2 extraction insert path and will
# be added (and audited) then.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google OAuth (issue #5) — the ONLY sign-in provider for the MVP.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These are read by the Supabase Auth server (GoTrue), NOT by the Next.js app
# bundle — they are PLACEHOLDER NAMES only, never real values in git. Supabase
# substitutes them into supabase/config.toml's [auth.external.google] via
# env(). Put the real values in .env.local (gitignored) for local dev; in prod
# they live in GCP Secret Manager and are bound to the hosted Supabase project.
#
# How to obtain them (one-time human setup — see README "Google OAuth setup"):
#   1. Google Cloud Console -> APIs & Services -> Credentials.
#   2. Create an OAuth 2.0 Client ID (type: Web application).
#   3. Authorized redirect URI must be the Supabase Auth callback:
#        local: http://127.0.0.1:54321/auth/v1/callback
#        prod : https://<project-ref>.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
#      (The app's own /auth/callback route is downstream of that; Supabase
#       redirects back to it. Local site_url/redirect allow-list is already set
#       in supabase/config.toml [auth].)
#   4. Copy the generated Client ID + Client secret into the two vars below.
#
# After setting these locally, restart the stack so the CLI picks them up:
#   npm run db:stop && npm run db:start
SUPABASE_AUTH_EXTERNAL_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-oauth-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
SUPABASE_AUTH_EXTERNAL_GOOGLE_SECRET=your-google-oauth-client-secret
